The cognomen of Juno referred to is Curitis, a word of Sabine origin, connected with curis or quiris, ‘ a spear.' honorem should probably be honore.

6. arcemur a religionis proprietate: ‘we are excluded from a right of possession in a religion of our own.' Proprietas bears its legal sense. Tertullian claims religious liberty in a civil sense for all. Yet the very nature of the Christian religion prevented it taking its place as a sister-religion to the national cults of the empire. Comp. Just. Mart. Apol. i. 243 Athenag. leq. pro Chr. 1. 14.
